Fill and boil your #kettle{}.

Halve the @green chilli{1/2}(halved lengthways, deseeded and finely chopped) lengthways, deseed and finely chop.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the boiling water into a large #saucepan{} on high heat, add @salt{1/2%tsp} and bring back to the boil.

Add the @spaghetti{180%g} to the boiling water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{8%minutes}.

Once cooked, reserve some @reserved pasta water{100%ml} for your sauce, then drain in a #colander{}.

Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g} and a pinch of the chopped chilli (careful, it's hot - add less if you'd prefer things milder). Cook, stirring, until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @king prawns{300%g} and cook for ~{2%minutes} more.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat and prawns.

Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add the reserved pasta water to the pan and stir through the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}.

Reduce the heat to low, then stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g} until well combined.

Simmer until the prawns are cooked through and the sauce is piping hot, another ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Add the cooked pasta to your creamy sauce and toss to coat, adding a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Serve your creamy prawn and bacon spaghetti pasta in #bowls{}.

Finish with a sprinkle of the remaining chilli if you'd like some more heat.

Enjoy!